# TURN server credentials for traversing symmetric NATs (VPN exits, corporate
# guest Wi-Fi, carrier-grade NAT). Without these, the app falls back to
# STUN-only ICE — fine for most home networks, fails on hostile ones.
#
# Setup:
# 1. Sign up at https://www.metered.ca (free tier: 50 GB/month) or any TURN
#    provider that gives you a URL + username + credential triple.
# 2. Copy this file to .env.local and fill in the values from the dashboard.
#    Metered hands you 4 URL variants for the same server (UDP/TCP on :80,
#    :443, and TLS on :443) — paste them all comma-separated; they share
#    one username/credential pair.
#
# WARNING: Vite bundles VITE_* env vars into the client JS. For `npm run dev`
# on localhost this is fine. If you `npm run build` and deploy a bundle that
# contains these values, the credentials leak to anyone viewing source and
# can be used to consume bandwidth on your TURN account. For production,
# mint short-lived per-session creds from a small server — see
# docs/known_limitations.md.
VITE_TURN_URLS=
VITE_TURN_USERNAME=
VITE_TURN_CREDENTIAL=
